ing": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/conservation-status-freshwater-species-and-habitats-key-biodiversity", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "The conservation status of freshwater species and habitats in Key Biodiversity Areas at the Sebou river basin", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/conservation-status-freshwater-species-and-habitats-key-biodiversity", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "979b286cf7cd1c4f31ea932c9538b3ff17bb092cbad5f0bd3a89c7df0ae64005"}, "3": {"node_id": "0e2ef051-271c-49f2-86df-59a697935fd4", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/conservation-status-freshwater-species-and-habitats-key-biodiversity", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "fee1ec9e1f4ca5085b8e47aae26bfb446c7945fc31541762a6be9ac481143023"}}, "hash": "8765a97174111e11db50e75da18bf6ecc6736732db7604191ad03fdb8e468fad", "text": "financing mechanism based on the payment for ecosystem services, contributing towards sustainable watershed management and the restoration of biodiversity and cultural activities. Six priority lakes with threatened water sources have been identified for implementation in the Sebou water fund, where the first round will focus on demonstrating how water and soil conservation management, sustainable agriculture and the protection of natural ecosystems contribute to the overall water supply in the Sebou basin. The Sebou river basin has a high value as a biodiversity hotspot. A total of 21 species found in this study were listed as threatened with extinction in the IUCN Red List. The lower section of the Bohlou river in the Tazekka natural park holds one of the best-recruiting populations of the freshwater mussel Pseudunio marocanus (assessed as Margaritifera marocana in the IUCN Red List) listed among the world\u2019s 100 most threatened species (Baillie & Butcher, 2012). To increase our knowledge on the freshwater biodiversity and especially the detected threatened species, further studies are necessary to get an overview of the full extent of the river basin (Nogueira et al., 2021). Priority areas for conservation of this freshwater biodiversity should be identified and listed as protected areas. Some of the sites in this study should be included as extension or as new Key Biodiversity Areas. Finally, some of the current KBA require more measures to protect freshwater biodiversity. It is important to ensure the continuation of correct management for the survival of threatened species in the assigned protected regions. Conclusions 6 The conservation status of freshwater species and habitats in Key Biodiversity Areas at the Sebou river basin 50 Amine, M.E.H.H.A., and El Kettani, Y. (2017). Construction of a Novel Water Quality Classifier: A case study in the Sebou region. International Journal of Applied Mathematics and Statistics, 56(5). Baillie, J., and Butcher, E. (2012). Priceless or Worthless? The world\u2019s most threatened species. Zoological Society of London, United Kingdom. BirdLife International (2021). The World Database of Key Biodiversity Areas. Developed by the KBA Partnership: BirdLife International, International Union for the Conservation of Nature, Amphibian Survival Alliance, Conservation International, Critical Ecosystem Partnership Fund, Global Environment Facility, Global Wildlife Conservation, NatureServe, Rainforest Trust, Royal Society for the Protection of Birds, Wildlife Conservation Society and World Wi